  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties & Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Providing sales and administrative support to operations.</p></li><li><p>Liaising with customer/agent enquiries.</p></li><li><p>Process and prepare sales orders, delivery order, logistics import and export documentation and collaborate with finance and operations on the payment collection.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with operations and logistics department to ensure timely deliveries from forwarder and suppliers.</p></li><li><p>Compile and generate monthly sales reports and weekly reports.</p></li><li><p>Preparing of purchase order to suppliers/principals.</p></li><li><p>Work on customer’s weekly delivery reschedule plan with principals.</p></li><li><p>Oversee office cleanliness and handle miscellaneous office issues as they arise.</p></li><li><p>Handle any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>At least Diploma in Business Administration or related field. </p></li><li><p>Fresh graduates are welcome, or 1-2 years of relevant experience in an administrative and purchasing.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency with Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook & PowerPoint). </p></li><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills (written and verbal). </p></li><li><p>Independent and able to work in a fast-paced environment and as part of a team. </p></li><li><p>Regular communication in English- and Mandarin-speaking clients and vendors.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge in Aerospace is an added advantage.</p></li></ul>",
